cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is about developing a full discourse parser in the Penn Discourse Treebank (PDTB) style. The PDTB is a widely used resource in computational linguistics and natural language processing, which makes the paper relevant to the cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-category. The paper also involves training a parser, which falls under the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. Additionally, the paper uses classification algorithms to classify relation types, which is relevant to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. The paper also involves locating and labeling arguments, which is relevant to the cs.IR (Information Retrieval) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves determining attribution spans, which is relevant to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category.
